definition: name/noun (part of speech)/place (e.g. among winners)/famous/classifier for people

sentences.english: So Madan and colleagues gave cellphones to 70 students in an undergraduate dormitory.
sentences.chinese: 因此馬丹與其同事給學校裏70名學生髮了手機。

sentences.english: The academic field which has developed to study placenames is called toponymy.
sentences.chinese: 而地名學就是以語言爲基本線索，研究地名的科學。

sentences.english: This article discussed the historical relations between toponymy and ancient nationality in HeiLongJiang Province.
sentences.chinese: 本文論述了黑龍江省地名學與古代民族的歷史關係。

sentences.english: There are also two architectural students.
sentences.chinese: 還有兩名學建築的學生。
